begin_memory_text: We talked about whether we had conversations in the past, where we live, and what we do for a living. We then talked about how we are both teachers and what we do.
middle_memory_text: We talked a lot about teaching and our specific jobs. How he's changed from teaching high school and is now a middle school teacher for at risk students. And about my job teaching community college. We talked a lot about how COVID is affecting our lives and jobs.
end_memory_text: We were still talking about our jobs and how things are going in our respective states (Wisconsin and Arizona) with COVID. He also thanked me for what I do as a community college math teacher and shared his experience as a high school math teacher.
rest_of_day_open: I think my week will go well. It won't be as stressful as the weeks in the past have been because I will have fewer classes starting Monday. I will have more time to get my prep work and grading done for my classes. And I will have more time to relax and enjoy some free time.
critical_positive: The conversation flowed pretty naturally. We didn't really have many lulls in the conversation. We had plenty of topics to talk about without it being awkward. We also had a lot in common as we are both teachers, so that meant we had a lot of things to talk about especially in a pandemic.
critical_negative: We sometimes talked over one another, so that was the biggest issue. Other than that, we didn't really have any other issues or difficulties. We both had a lot to say, so it was sometimes hard to get a word in. But at the same time, sometimes I felt like I rambled on too much.

begin_memory_text: At the beginning we talked about where we lived and which sports teams we followed. She followed the Padres and I follow the brewers, She lives in AZ which is the spring training home of the Brewers, We also mentioned Tony Gwyn who played for the Padres and his son played for the Brewers.
middle_memory_text: In the middle we talked about teaching. She was a professor at a community college. She teaches Math to new students and students at the end of the program. We discussed Zoom and its impact on our teaching.
end_memory_text: At the end we discussed COVID-19 and how it is very scary. We also talked on a desire for normalcy and a getting through this. We both said that time went very fast and that we enjoyed the conversations.
rest_of_day_open: I think the week will go well. There were a couple of big things that have been resolved and the next week should be good. I am looking forward to spending time with my family and helping my students. I know that Covid will make things tough, but that we will get through it.
critical_positive: We were both sports fans, that also liked working with learners. Our shared careers made it very easy to talk about life and about our current jobs. Since we both avoided politics and religion, we were able to focus on things that were not contentious. We both listened to each other and made sure that each person was able to talk.
critical_negative: There were a couple of times where we were at a loss for words. We didn't get into a deep talk but stuck to rather safe conversations. That is understandable considering were just met. I think deeper conversations could be had if participants spoke to each other more than once. I think it was a very nice situation and I enjoyed it.
